        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 4:23PM EDT by NWS Wilmington OH</headline>
        <description>At 422 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located near Kings Island,
moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Hail may cause minor damage to
vegetation.

Locations impacted include...
Mason, Lebanon, Wilmington, Loveland, Blanchester, Morrow, Kings
Island, South Lebanon, Maineville, Clarksville, Harveysburg, Goshen,
Martinsville, Midland, Butlerville, Pleasant Plain, Murdock, State
Route 123 at State Route 132, Fort Ancient, and Oakland.

This includes I-71 in Ohio between mile markers 22 and 50.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a sturdy building.

To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.
</description>
